 <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=24935>Slagfest "The Warlord" Bloodsoul</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uiskandaralazeem.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iskandar Alazeem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of the Battlefield</BR>STEEL WARRIOR Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 794<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/10/02 2:31:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3858.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.purgatory.net/alex/images/seph_mug_01.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Equiping a MT...</span><hr size=1> From looking at this with the facts you've given, I personally think that loot decision is ass. Being passed up for loot when you've paid your dues is one of the worst feelings you can experience in EQ.<br>
<br>
I'm all for merit - your rewards are roughly equivalent to your contributions and overall attitude. But, that's just what I prefer. Bottom line: whatever your particular guild thinks is most fair is best.<br>
<br>
-Isk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uquargo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quargo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/10/02 2:56:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3858.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Equiping a MT...</span><hr size=1> My guild generally follows the guidelines of &quot;whoever it'll be the biggest upgrade for, gets it.&quot; Although, this isnt followed strictly by any means; things like time spent in the guild, how often you raid, how long it's been since ya got any loot, and your level/# of aa's will also be a factor.<br>
<br>
I think just decking out 1 tank is bad. You can do it to an extent, though.. Like say a 41% haste item drops, and yer MT only has like a 31-36ish% haste item than you may want to just give it to them because of the large impact it will have on their tanking abilities. Other than that, especially since practically everything good is no drop, its better to give things to the person that it'll upgrade most cuz it raises the whole guild's HP/AC/stats/whatever the most, as opposed to being a small upgrade to your MT. Besides that, people will start to get real pissy if they go for months without getting jack while they keep seeing you pile the 10-20hp upgrades onto your MT while it'd be a 100hp upgrade for someone else <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=51736" target="_new">Quarg Poopybunz</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uxenojones.showPublicProfile?language=EN>XENOJONES</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 280<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/11/02 1:05:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3858.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Equiping a MT...</span><hr size=1> If you can trust the MT to stay in the guild and work for the guild then get behind him and ride on his back if not you probably shouldn't have guilded him in the first place.<br>
<br>
<br>
Rollen<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Our guild is almost totally assigned loot and with stuff almost all tradeable on FV it allows us to continuously upgrade the MTs and pass equiptment down. This would not work well on otehr servers. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uuthuk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Uthuk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/11/02 1:06:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3858.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Equiping a MT...</span><hr size=1> If you want to raid alot and progress at a decent rate you need to equip some people outside the merit system.<br>
<br>
MT: <br>
You need 3-5 warriors in good gear and these need to play at a regular time, say 70% of all raids. At start this means giveing them +20 hp upgrades while dmg dealers dont get to upgrade +100 hp. <br>
<br>
If you have the option also deck out a pal/sk or two but once again you have to find people that play regularly on raids or its a waste of guild resources.<br>
<br>
There are some other classes that need to be given priority too like wiz/cle for mana pool and FT items.<br>
<br>
If you dont mind lagging behind though you can keep decking all the members but it will take alot longer before you manage to progress in encounters.<br>
 <p>Nirre
60 warrior
Xev</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ufoolsfizzelmore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fools Fizzelmore</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 100<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/11/02 3:45:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3858.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://fools.spyd.net/cuch.swf WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Equiping a MT...</span><hr size=1> For us we have one war who is equiped in the best gear first. It is logical if somone is trustworthy and attends 90% of raids then it is in the GUILDS best interest to equip him first. (it also helps if the MT in question shares his info with the GL and officers so they can log him in if needed).<br>
<br>
It is best to have 3 or so wars in the best you can get them and then start fitting out the rest of the guild.<br>
<br>
One war up there with 7500+ hps is better than having 10 people with 6k-6.5k hps.<br>
<br>
Having said that....if someone is a new addition to a guild and they stat looking for the best the guild can get from day 1...that is not a good sign. I would be carefull of new people who are in it just for the loot. Having said that..if that person is willing to moniter DN until vaniki is up and then ask for the guild help then cool. It is a different matter if he expects the guild to monitor the spawn for him so he can swoop in for the loots.<br>
<br>
If you have issues with a new addition starting to look for all the loots, then talk with your officers and GL. It is always a good idea to express your concerns before anything bad happens.<br>
<br>
cuch <p><p><center><B><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=78052 ">Cuchullan</A><br>Warlord<br><A HREF="http://www.insidiousblood.net/">IB</A></b></center></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=thoric>Thoric</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 48<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/11/02 4:02:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3858.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   re: Equiping a MT...</span><hr size=1> It's never a good idea to be totally reliant on 1 person.  Even with the best equipped tanks available, tank switches are still necessary sometimes, and you don't want a severe dropoff when SA steps up.<br>
