I also don't think it's a great idea to award loot to a new member (especially if it will be a huge upgrade as you seem to suggest the vindi bp would be for your guild tanks).  Just a slap in the face to the tanks who put the time in. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wychway>Wychway</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 148<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/11/02 6:50:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3858.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: re: Equiping a MT...</span><hr size=1> I personally do not like this method. We already know we are not damage dealers. Having multiple warriors with only one or two geared up with all the best to tank things, a couple more as add tanks, the rest of us might as well reroll monks or rogues or something. All this method is good for is a fast start, though the result debatable. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=91801">Wychway Darkmink</a><BR>Inky Warlady, Bristlebane<BR><br>Facts:<br>1. Minks are mammals.<br> 
2. Minks fight ALL the time.<br>
3. The purpose of a mink is to flip out and kill people.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/upokiri.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pokiri</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/11/02 7:25:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3858.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Equiping a MT...</span><hr size=1> Raun - email me (pokiri@swordoffate.com), you don't have the whole story, and neither does anyone else that's posting here (no offense).<br>
