its crappy <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7023  target="web">smushums<a</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uleod.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Leod</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/13/02 2:25:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3858.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Equiping a MT...</span><hr size=1> IMO, it's *completely* up to your guild's style. From the sounds of it, your either a non-raid guild, or your a new guild just getting their feet under them (or atleast new to the high end game).<br>
<br>
I'm in a non-raid guild. We're a gaming guild, actually in 5 different games right now, strongest in EQ. Been around 5 years, so we're very very mature and have a strong family atmosphere. We actually let the raid leader make all decisions about loot awards, but usually on big stuff either I'm leading, or there is a committe.<br>
<br>
We do alot of things with friends, could say allied guilds I guess. To give you an idea where we sit, we've done vindi 10+ times, done rumble/Doom, and I've successfully lead the 10th Ring War twice now (new changes make it quick!).<br>
<br>
The let the raid leader award things works for us. We don't have any 7k hp tanks, but we do have 4-5 tanks ni the 6-6.5k range now, and for where we sit on the ladder (about to hit VP), that's plenty for us (and we'd have a hard time getting any tank to 7k hp without NToV Loot, which we haven't entered yet).<br>
<br>
